# Copy this file to  leak-patterns.local  (which is gitignored) and add the
# literal strings that must NEVER reach this public repo: employer name,
# internal project codenames, a private hostname, etc.
#
# One ERE per line; matched case-insensitively. Whole-line '#' comments and
# blank lines are ignored. Do NOT list strings that are intentionally public
# (your name in LICENSE/pyproject, your commit email) — that would block honest
# commits to those files.
#
# Examples (replace with your own, then delete these):
# Acme Corporation
# Acme-Corporation
# project-bluebird
# 10\.0\.0\.42
